02:42.371 --> 02:44.373
Hello?

02:48.252 --> 02:50.254
Is someone there?

02:52.214 --> 02:54.216
Is someone in there?

02:56.718 --> 02:58.929
Is there someone
alive in there?

03:16.864 --> 03:18.907
Hey.

03:18.949 --> 03:19.950
Are you okay?

03:20.993 --> 03:23.203
Are you okay?

03:24.329 --> 03:26.373
I'm gonna get you
out of there.

03:28.959 --> 03:30.544
Hold on!

04:29.728 --> 04:32.606
What does it mean
to be happy?

04:35.025 --> 04:38.320
To be content
in the world around you?

04:42.199 --> 04:44.660
Mom used to say
it was family--

04:47.538 --> 04:51.333
That family is the heart
of everything, even existence.

04:51.375 --> 04:54.628
Without it, there's nothing.

04:58.549 --> 05:00.801
She would always have
these simple answers

05:00.843 --> 05:03.512
that somehow would sound
so brilliant.

05:07.599 --> 05:09.977
And then she died.

05:10.978 --> 05:13.939
My father died
along with her.

05:14.940 --> 05:18.026
Shortly after that, my brother David
had to sell the farm

05:18.068 --> 05:20.487
where we grew up.

05:22.614 --> 05:25.367
Now we're just trying to be
an ordinary family,

05:25.409 --> 05:29.454
trying to figure out
where we fit in in the world.

05:33.500 --> 05:35.502
And for me,

05:35.544 --> 05:37.921
I'm trying to figure out
where I belong,

05:37.963 --> 05:41.258
right now
in this exact moment.

05:41.884 --> 05:44.219
I don't know, Dad.
What do you think about the black hair?

05:47.973 --> 05:49.766
Come on, it's different.

05:49.808 --> 05:52.144
- It's different than normal.
- It's pretty, don't you think?

05:54.646 --> 05:57.065
Oh, yes.
Yes yes, definitely--

05:57.107 --> 05:58.901
right there, right there.

05:58.942 --> 06:01.028
Look at the baby,
he's part of the family.

06:01.069 --> 06:03.405
- Hey, there we go.
- Okay, Dad.

06:24.301 --> 06:26.136
I don't wanna hear that,
Darlene.

06:26.178 --> 06:28.055
The social worker
will be here tomorrow.

06:28.096 --> 06:29.973
We can't have the place
looking like this.

06:30.015 --> 06:33.727
- Whatever you say, Dad.
- That's not funny, Darlene.

06:33.769 --> 06:36.480
Okay, I'm trying to do
the best I can here.

06:36.522 --> 06:38.941
Oh, Jesus. You know, I'm not
a little girl anymore

06:38.982 --> 06:40.943
and you don't have to be
a dick about this!

06:40.984 --> 06:43.320
Just-- can you just please
clean your room

06:43.362 --> 06:46.114
and maybe not wear that mess
on your eyes tomorrow?

06:46.156 --> 06:48.116
Fuck you, David!

06:54.665 --> 06:57.417
Francis, turn it off now!

06:57.459 --> 07:00.087
Oh, come on, David,
it's a school project.

07:00.128 --> 07:02.297
- Just not our personal stuff, okay?
- It's about our family.

07:02.339 --> 07:05.008
- I need this kind of stuff.
- Turn it off now!

07:08.262 --> 07:11.390
You just get the heck
out of my face for a second.

07:15.227 --> 07:17.813
My brother David
is the oldest.

07:17.855 --> 07:21.817
He picked up all the responsibilities
after Mom and Dad died.

07:23.110 --> 07:25.279
We used to be real close,

07:26.822 --> 07:30.492
but after he sold our farm
something changed in him.

07:30.534 --> 07:34.496
He became like one of those life-sized
cardboard cutouts you see in the stores,

07:34.538 --> 07:38.959
trying to sell the idea
that everything is perfect,

07:40.210 --> 07:43.213
but really nothing
is the same anymore.

07:43.213 --> 07:45.424
We just keep moving
from town to town

07:45.465 --> 07:47.384
running from the truth,

07:47.384 --> 07:50.470
waiting for it to one day
catch up with us.

07:51.555 --> 07:54.516
This is our sixth house
in two years.

08:23.128 --> 08:25.214
Oh, yeah,
every single one of them.

08:26.256 --> 08:29.426
Wow, that's cool.

08:29.468 --> 08:31.553
Okay, guys,
I'm gonna go pee.

08:31.595 --> 08:33.931
- No, wait.
- I gotta go. No, come on.

08:33.931 --> 08:36.517
- Sam, stay.
- I'm gonna go. I'll be right back.

08:36.558 --> 08:40.270
- Don't take too long.
- I won't.

09:24.857 --> 09:29.027
Sam, get your ass in here
and smoke a joint.

09:29.069 --> 09:32.990
It's beautiful. Come on,
do the rain dance.

09:33.031 --> 09:35.492
Hell, no! Get in the car
right now, girl.

09:35.534 --> 09:37.995
Come on. No!

09:39.079 --> 09:42.624
- Yeah! Ow! Get in here.
- Come on!

09:42.666 --> 09:45.043
Back in.

09:46.879 --> 09:50.841
So, did you guys have fun?

09:50.841 --> 09:52.843
- Yeah.
- You are glowing.

09:52.843 --> 09:55.012
No, I'm not.

09:57.222 --> 10:01.059
So, Wendell,
what do you do?

10:02.853 --> 10:05.439
I work for my brother--

10:06.690 --> 10:09.318
fetch stuff for him,
things like that.

10:09.359 --> 10:13.780
- Nothing too exciting though.
- Sounds cool.

10:14.990 --> 10:18.285
So where are you guys off
to next, huh?

10:18.327 --> 10:20.787
Seattle, I think.

10:20.829 --> 10:23.457
We're just gonna keep traveling
city to city

10:23.498 --> 10:26.460
till we run all out of money.

10:27.461 --> 10:30.631
- Can't beat that kind of freedom.
- No, we just picked up and left!

10:30.672 --> 10:32.049
No one even knows
where we're at.

10:32.049 --> 10:34.301
- What?
- Hush.

10:34.343 --> 10:36.720
We don't have to worry
about Wendell, our hero.

10:36.762 --> 10:39.890
Wendell is Superman.

10:43.519 --> 10:46.813
Wow, look at that.

10:46.855 --> 10:49.149
Look at all
those pretty stars.

10:49.191 --> 10:52.861
- Where?
- I think you mean raindrops.

11:24.434 --> 11:27.062
You can at least pretend
to like it, okay?

11:30.440 --> 11:34.444
Hey, I'm sorry for yelling
at you yesterday.

11:34.486 --> 11:37.239
I didn't mean to.

11:37.281 --> 11:39.491
We're good?

11:39.533 --> 11:43.745
Yeah, we're good. But, David,
I'm really not feeling too hot today.

11:43.787 --> 11:46.456
- You're going to school, okay?
- I just don't think--

11:46.498 --> 11:48.417
I don't wanna hear it.
You're going to school.

11:48.458 --> 11:51.962
Good morning, sleepyhead.
You want some breakfast?

11:52.004 --> 11:54.631
Why do you even bother?

11:56.133 --> 11:59.678
Because that's what families do.
They have breakfast together.

11:59.720 --> 12:03.432
Cute, David. Anyway, Kitty's
spending the night tomorrow.

12:03.473 --> 12:05.809
- Who's uh--
- I am telling you in advance,

12:05.809 --> 12:08.604
- just like you asked.
- Who the heck is Kitty?

12:08.645 --> 12:11.356
I don't know,
some chick from Ohio.

12:11.398 --> 12:15.485
All right. Remember, social worker
is coming tonight at 5:00 for dinner.

12:19.156 --> 12:22.242
You should really try
giving up cooking, David.

12:25.829 --> 12:28.457
I'm off,
and you go to school.

12:28.498 --> 12:30.292
I really don't fit in there.

12:30.334 --> 12:32.294
Look,

12:34.505 --> 12:36.757
I know it's hard for you,

12:36.798 --> 12:38.926
but can you please
at least try?

12:38.967 --> 12:42.471
Why? It's not my fault
we're always moving.

12:42.513 --> 12:45.849
You're right, Francis.
It's my fault.

12:45.849 --> 12:48.602
I'm sorry, guys.

12:48.644 --> 12:52.231
I know I have a bad temper.
What do you want me to do?

12:53.482 --> 12:56.568
Some maybe say I'm bipolar.

12:56.610 --> 13:00.239
Good morning, Francis.
How are you doing there, bud, huh?

13:00.280 --> 13:02.282
What are you reading?

13:02.324 --> 13:05.994
"Gay sperm donors needed
for lesbian couple."

13:06.036 --> 13:08.997
- Knock it off.
- You're calling that today.

13:14.378 --> 13:17.297
- Have you fed Lenny?
- Don't look at me. Look at Franny.

13:17.339 --> 13:20.008
Oh, come on, I just did it
two days ago.

13:20.050 --> 13:22.177
Okay, I gotta go to work.

13:22.219 --> 13:26.473
- Will you just please do it?
- I'll do it before I go to school.

13:30.060 --> 13:33.939
Where're you going? Oh, yeah, you gotta
go do your thing. Forgot, sorry.

13:33.981 --> 13:36.692
Have fun.
Have a good day.

13:39.903 --> 13:44.408
The twins-- they've always
been distant from the family.

13:44.449 --> 13:47.744
Wendell is the main reason
why we move a lot.

13:47.786 --> 13:50.080
He just got out of jail for biting
some guy's ear off

13:50.122 --> 13:53.458
at a Cheesy Chuck's Pizza parlor
up north.

13:53.500 --> 13:57.004
Darlene is just as mean,
but more refined.

13:57.045 --> 14:00.048
Like when we were kids,
she used to lock me in the closet

14:00.090 --> 14:02.593
just to hear me scream.
Then, hours later,

14:02.634 --> 14:06.430
she would let me out pretending
she was the one who saved me.

14:06.471 --> 14:09.224
And I always fell for it.

14:58.315 --> 15:00.943
Let me out of here!

15:00.984 --> 15:04.112
Help, please!

15:33.851 --> 15:35.811
Please.

15:38.105 --> 15:42.317
Somebody please help us!

15:51.994 --> 15:55.747
Oh, heck no, we've had a lot
of social workers come here,

15:55.789 --> 15:58.041
but you're the first
for dinner.

15:58.083 --> 16:01.712
So, Francis, what's up
with you tonight, huh?

16:02.713 --> 16:05.299
- Nothing.
- Anything you wanna talk about?

16:05.340 --> 16:08.343
Anything at all? School maybe?
I don't know...

16:10.220 --> 16:13.891
Well, you know, if there is,
you just jump on in, all right?

16:13.932 --> 16:16.852
Yeah, he told me he wasn't
feeling too well this morning.

16:16.894 --> 16:19.021
Oh, I'm sorry.

16:19.062 --> 16:21.899
Oh, thank you, Darlene.

16:21.940 --> 16:24.568
That's, uh... quite a creative look

16:24.610 --> 16:27.112
you've got going there,
young lady.

16:27.154 --> 16:29.990
- What do you call that, huh?
- Death.

16:31.033 --> 16:34.661
Ah, death. That's cute.

16:35.746 --> 16:38.373
So tell me, David,
are you and Wendell

16:38.415 --> 16:42.544
still working over there
at Del Rancho?

16:42.586 --> 16:45.047
I don't know if I could work
at a slaughterhouse, huh?

16:45.088 --> 16:47.883
Yeah, well, my father
owned a farm

16:47.925 --> 16:50.552
when we were younger
and he did the same thing,

16:50.594 --> 16:53.055
so I guess it just
came naturally.

16:53.096 --> 16:55.057
Well...

16:56.099 --> 16:59.728
so, like, what do they have you
doing over there?

16:59.770 --> 17:01.730
I mean...

17:03.065 --> 17:06.944
you don't have to kill the animals
and all that stuff, do you, David?

17:06.944 --> 17:10.155
Heavens, no.
No no, I'm a carver.

17:10.196 --> 17:13.200
I take out the organs,
prep them, stuff like that.

17:13.242 --> 17:17.287
Yes, David has a real knack
for gutting the life out of things.

17:17.329 --> 17:19.414
Thank you, Darlene.

17:22.125 --> 17:24.962
So... too bad there's not--

17:25.002 --> 17:27.964
not a demand
on the black market for cow parts.

17:28.006 --> 17:31.593
You would be a rich man
by now.

17:31.635 --> 17:34.012
Not at the table,
please, Francis.

17:34.054 --> 17:38.433
I apologize. Paul, he's been
following us around with that thing

17:38.475 --> 17:41.687
for the past few days--
some sort of school project

17:41.728 --> 17:43.981
- or something or other.
- No, that's fine with me.

17:44.022 --> 17:48.026
I think it's kind of cool.
Francis, tell me about the project.

17:49.278 --> 17:52.656
Well, it's uh--

17:52.656 --> 17:57.119
I'm supposed to write
a report about my family--

17:57.160 --> 17:58.787
our family--

17:58.829 --> 18:03.417
and I just asked if I could
shoot a video instead.

18:03.458 --> 18:07.838
Good. Now, that's a good idea.
That is a great idea.

18:07.838 --> 18:09.923
- I hated doing papers. I hated it.
- Me too.

18:09.965 --> 18:11.633
I really did.

18:11.675 --> 18:13.886
- Hey, gang.
- Hey, Wendell.

18:13.927 --> 18:14.970
- Hey.
- How are you?

18:15.012 --> 18:18.140
- Good, Paul. How are you?
- Good, thanks.

18:18.182 --> 18:20.809
Am I late?

18:20.851 --> 18:23.312
What do you think,
Wendell?

18:23.353 --> 18:26.857
David,
may I please be excused?

18:26.899 --> 18:29.026
- We're not finished eating.
- No no no, let the boy go.

18:29.067 --> 18:30.819
- Mm-hmm.
- He's probably bored out of his mind.

18:30.861 --> 18:33.780
- Where are you going, Francis?
- I used to have two younger brothers,

18:33.822 --> 18:35.782
so I understand these things.

18:35.824 --> 18:38.368
They are a handful.

18:58.764 --> 19:02.226
That was great, you guys.
Thanks a lot.

19:02.267 --> 19:04.895
I know I'm not much
of a cook, but I do try.

19:04.937 --> 19:08.649
Not to worry. You probably never
tasted my wife's cooking, huh?

19:14.947 --> 19:19.076
Well, I'll be in the kitchen
cleaning.

19:26.291 --> 19:28.544
Did you hear that?

19:31.171 --> 19:34.174
Oh, it's probably cats...

19:34.216 --> 19:36.718
fucking.

19:38.762 --> 19:41.932
Yep, that's cats
fucking, all right--

19:41.974 --> 19:45.602
getting after it.
What do you think, David?

19:48.438 --> 19:51.066
Who'd have thought?

19:51.108 --> 19:53.068
- Listen, that was a great dinner.
- Thank you.

19:53.110 --> 19:54.736
- I'll talk to you soon.
- Thanks. Yeah.

19:54.778 --> 19:56.530
- Thanks, David.
- Good night, Paul.

19:56.572 --> 19:58.866
Good night.

20:24.308 --> 20:27.853
Need more padding on that south wall.
You can hear 'em upstairs.

20:28.854 --> 20:32.107
All right, so you're sure
that they're good?

20:32.149 --> 20:34.234
Positive. On a road trip,

20:34.276 --> 20:37.112
it's gonna be two, three weeks
before anyone notices.

20:37.154 --> 20:39.573
- Healthy?
- Oh, yeah.

20:39.615 --> 20:42.993
- I even took one for a test drive.
- Quit acting up, okay?

20:42.993 --> 20:46.288
I don't want their faces showing up
on the 10:00 news like last time.

20:46.330 --> 20:49.166
- This could sustain us for awhile.
- Trust me.

20:50.167 --> 20:52.586
All right.
Let's get to work.

21:01.136 --> 21:04.348
- Help.
- Room service.

21:07.643 --> 21:10.979
How are we holding up, girls?
Good?

21:14.775 --> 21:17.861
Well, you're
looking good. Hi.

21:20.822 --> 21:23.158
I hope this doesn't change
anything between us.

21:23.200 --> 21:25.577
Wendell, what did I tell you?

21:27.162 --> 21:30.082
Come on, sweetheart.

21:30.123 --> 21:32.501
- Stop it!
- Come on.

21:32.543 --> 21:35.128
Get up.
Oh, yeah!

21:35.170 --> 21:36.880
Don't worry, Sam.

21:36.922 --> 21:40.592
I still got something
right here, okay?

21:40.634 --> 21:43.262
All right, let's
get you up, huh?

21:43.303 --> 21:45.180
You're a live one,
aren't you?

21:45.222 --> 21:48.684
Let's tie you down here.
Let's get you down here.

21:57.818 --> 21:59.862
Is that too tight, sweetie?

22:15.460 --> 22:18.505
- Sounds like he's changing.
- Hey. Hey, Lenny.

22:19.798 --> 22:23.177
Poor guy's
probably hungry.

22:23.218 --> 22:27.055
We'll feed him later.
Just go keep watch.

22:28.891 --> 22:31.685
I'm gonna tuck you in
later, okay?

22:32.811 --> 22:34.354
I got you.

24:00.983 --> 24:03.151
Get in. I'll give you
a ride to school.

24:04.152 --> 24:07.573
I saw some stuff
I want to shoot, Wendell.

24:07.614 --> 24:09.616
Just get the fuck in.

24:10.701 --> 24:13.120
God damn.

24:17.875 --> 24:21.170
You gotta pop your cherry,
baby brother.

24:21.211 --> 24:23.172
Huh?

24:24.423 --> 24:28.385
So you can quit moping around,
playing with that camera.

24:30.888 --> 24:34.474
Hey! Hey.

24:34.516 --> 24:36.852
What, are you too good
to talk to me now?

24:38.854 --> 24:41.690
- Fuck you, Wendell!
- What?!

24:41.732 --> 24:43.859
- What the-- hey! Hey!
- Fuck you!

24:43.901 --> 24:45.194
- Keep it up, Francis!
- No!

24:45.235 --> 24:48.947
Keep it up! We take care
of your sorry ass, all right?

24:48.989 --> 24:51.825
We feed you, we put fucking clothes
on your back,

24:51.867 --> 24:54.786
and you do nothing in return
but complain.

24:54.828 --> 24:56.872
Let go of me!

24:59.958 --> 25:02.044
Dude, l-- look,

25:02.085 --> 25:05.088
I know it fucking seems
fucked up, all right?

25:05.088 --> 25:07.716
But we do what we do

25:07.758 --> 25:09.760
to survive.

25:10.928 --> 25:12.930
All right?

25:15.015 --> 25:18.852
You do anything to fuck up
our family-- most importantly me--

25:18.894 --> 25:21.980
I'll fucking kill you, okay?

25:22.022 --> 25:24.650
Hey! Okay?

25:25.651 --> 25:27.653
Get the fuck out of my truck.

25:54.429 --> 25:58.058
Shut the fuck up
before I gut you myself!

26:15.701 --> 26:17.703
Bye, Lenny.

27:17.721 --> 27:19.681
Hello?

27:22.017 --> 27:24.478
Anybody home?

27:33.403 --> 27:35.697
Yes, hello.
This is David Hamilton.

27:35.739 --> 27:38.242
I'm calling on behalf
of Francis Hamilton.

27:38.242 --> 27:42.079
Yes yes. Yeah,
he's not feeling too well,

27:42.120 --> 27:44.456
got a case of the flu
or something.

27:44.498 --> 27:46.166
Yeah, right right.

27:46.208 --> 27:48.168
Oh, thank you,
I appreciate it.

27:48.210 --> 27:50.337
Have a great day. Bye.

28:18.782 --> 28:22.494
Please don't hurt her
anymore.

28:24.162 --> 28:26.290
I'm not like them.

28:28.166 --> 28:31.420
Then can you help us,
please?

28:36.884 --> 28:39.052
I'm sorry, but I can't.

28:40.053 --> 28:44.224
- Please.
- I don't even have a key.

28:44.266 --> 28:47.144
Do something, please.

28:49.438 --> 28:52.608
I can give you
something to drink.

28:52.649 --> 28:54.860
Do you want
something to drink?

29:47.246 --> 29:49.998
She needs some, please.

29:51.375 --> 29:53.502
I don't have a key.

29:53.544 --> 29:56.046
She just needs water.
She's dying.

29:58.590 --> 30:01.552
I have to go.
Someone will be here soon.

30:09.852 --> 30:11.186
Please.

31:12.789 --> 31:15.417
The top drawer, eh?

31:24.301 --> 31:25.969
You need a fake ID?

31:26.011 --> 31:27.930
Where did you get all those?

31:27.971 --> 31:30.015
I know a guy in the city.

31:30.057 --> 31:32.601
You want one?
I won't charge you.

31:32.643 --> 31:35.270
Yeah.

31:35.312 --> 31:37.898
Let's see.

31:37.940 --> 31:40.609
>>DRIVER LICENSE<<
Here we go-- Dani Cummings.

31:40.651 --> 31:44.404
Oh, look she's an organ donor.
How sweet!

31:44.446 --> 31:46.448
Seems about your height...

31:46.490 --> 31:48.534
- Blonde hair.
- That's okay.

31:48.575 --> 31:51.328
What are you little girls doing?

31:51.370 --> 31:54.122
We are just getting comfortable

31:54.164 --> 31:56.166
and throwing in a flick.

31:56.208 --> 31:58.460
You wanna watch?

31:58.502 --> 32:01.839
I'd love to watch.

32:06.844 --> 32:08.303
Where were you, Francis?

32:08.345 --> 32:11.139
I was just down by the river

32:11.181 --> 32:13.141
filming some stuff.

32:13.183 --> 32:15.269
Pretty late, huh?

32:15.310 --> 32:17.479
Yeah, I guess.

32:17.521 --> 32:19.314
Well, I'm going out
for a little bit.

32:23.694 --> 32:25.988
So if you need anything...

32:27.698 --> 32:29.658
All right.

32:31.076 --> 32:33.078
All right. I'll see you later.

33:42.439 --> 33:45.234
Turn it off, turn it off!

33:46.777 --> 33:49.196
It's just a movie, sweetheart.

33:49.238 --> 33:51.240
I thought you liked
this kind of stuff.

