how do you explain that?

01:03:37.609 --> 01:03:40.112
Are you that blind in your
make-believe world,

01:03:40.153 --> 01:03:41.989
you don't think we know?

01:03:42.030 --> 01:03:44.157
I use my head!

01:03:44.199 --> 01:03:46.994
I pick transients
and drifters,

01:03:47.035 --> 01:03:49.830
not some neighborhood girl
whose cousin or--

01:03:49.872 --> 01:03:52.249
or brother or whatever
is the police!

01:03:52.291 --> 01:03:55.169
You know why you hate us
so much, David?

01:03:55.210 --> 01:03:58.213
It's because
we represent everything

01:03:58.255 --> 01:04:00.048
you wish you could have,

01:04:00.090 --> 01:04:03.343
but are just too afraid
to face.

01:04:18.942 --> 01:04:21.320
You two always--

01:04:21.361 --> 01:04:23.071
fuck it up!

01:04:23.113 --> 01:04:27.201
Are you trying
to scare us, David,

01:04:27.242 --> 01:04:30.245
like when we were kids?

01:04:30.287 --> 01:04:32.581
We're not little kids anymore.

01:04:32.623 --> 01:04:34.708
So what are you
gonna do, David?

01:04:34.750 --> 01:04:36.877
When are you gonna realize
this isn't the first time

01:04:36.919 --> 01:04:40.088
and certainly not the last time
it's gonna happen?

01:04:40.130 --> 01:04:42.716
Pull it together.

01:04:42.758 --> 01:04:44.718
Hey!

01:04:47.846 --> 01:04:50.807
- Mom and Dad--
- Mom and Dad were the exception.

01:04:50.849 --> 01:04:54.561
None of us have the kind
of self-control to have what they did.

01:04:54.603 --> 01:04:56.772
The only difference
between you and us, David,

01:04:56.813 --> 01:04:59.107
is we don't look at ourselves
in the mirror and lie.

01:04:59.149 --> 01:05:01.693
We accept who we are.

01:05:01.735 --> 01:05:03.445
We don't deny it.

01:05:05.739 --> 01:05:08.075
We have to move again.

01:05:12.371 --> 01:05:15.999
All right, pack up
what we need--

01:06:28.989 --> 01:06:30.657
- Hi, this is Paul.
- Hey, Paul--

01:06:30.699 --> 01:06:32.618
Please leave your message
at the sound of the tone.

01:06:32.659 --> 01:06:35.370
Don't forget to leave
your phone number. Bye.

01:06:35.412 --> 01:06:37.414
Paul, it's Francis.

01:06:37.456 --> 01:06:40.417
There's something really important
we gotta talk about

01:06:40.459 --> 01:06:43.378
about my family
and um...

01:06:43.420 --> 01:06:46.131
I can't-- I can't do it
over the phone.

01:06:46.173 --> 01:06:48.383
If you could meet me in person,
that'd be great.

01:06:48.425 --> 01:06:50.928
l-l-I just--
fuck!

01:06:50.969 --> 01:06:52.971
I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

01:07:15.452 --> 01:07:18.205
I know, Lenny.
I know.

01:07:18.247 --> 01:07:20.874
It's coming.

01:07:20.916 --> 01:07:23.919
It's coming, Lenny!
Please sit still.

01:08:08.338 --> 01:08:10.841
Actually, it's--
it's kind of funny.

01:08:10.883 --> 01:08:14.636
My father taught me
how to do this.

01:08:14.678 --> 01:08:16.721
It's kooky, I know,
I know.

01:08:16.763 --> 01:08:19.515
He just wanted to make sure
if something were to happen to him,

01:08:19.558 --> 01:08:21.852
we'd still survive.

01:08:22.895 --> 01:08:26.982
Now you gotta get it
just right, so no air gets in.

01:08:28.024 --> 01:08:30.527
It has a longer shelf life
that way.

01:08:31.528 --> 01:08:33.529
It's kind of like...

01:08:35.073 --> 01:08:37.075
frozen food.

01:08:38.368 --> 01:08:40.370
You have something
on your face there.

01:08:40.412 --> 01:08:42.163
Oh, I apologize,

01:08:42.206 --> 01:08:45.250
I don't mean to make you
self-conscious or anything.

01:08:46.877 --> 01:08:48.837
"David," he said,
"David--

01:08:48.879 --> 01:08:52.381
David, one day
you might have to be

01:08:52.424 --> 01:08:54.426
the man of this family.

01:08:57.554 --> 01:08:59.555
David...

01:08:59.555 --> 01:09:02.017
David," he said--
he said, "David,

01:09:02.059 --> 01:09:05.354
you might have to be
the one that takes care

01:09:05.395 --> 01:09:07.856
of your brothers
and your sister."

01:09:08.941 --> 01:09:11.318
And I do, I do,

01:09:11.359 --> 01:09:13.987
but they don't care.

01:09:14.029 --> 01:09:16.323
Do you think they appreciate
what I do for them?

01:09:16.365 --> 01:09:20.035
No no no no.

01:09:26.625 --> 01:09:28.877
Look, missy,

01:09:28.919 --> 01:09:31.380
I don't mean to be a rude cunt,
but it sort of seems to me

01:09:31.421 --> 01:09:34.216
that you're not listening
to me.

01:09:34.258 --> 01:09:36.385
I just want
what's best for them.

01:09:37.761 --> 01:09:39.846
I just want what's
best for them.

01:09:39.888 --> 01:09:42.975
I just want
what's best for them.

01:10:19.386 --> 01:10:21.680
Goodbye, Lenny.

01:11:05.891 --> 01:11:07.893
Francis?

01:11:10.938 --> 01:11:12.940
Hey, Francis,
I got your message.

01:11:17.611 --> 01:11:20.197
Francis?

01:11:31.375 --> 01:11:34.127
David, are you here?
Francis?

01:11:38.507 --> 01:11:40.467
Francis?

01:11:44.429 --> 01:11:46.431
Francis, is that you?

01:11:49.434 --> 01:11:51.562
Francis, you out here?

01:12:28.390 --> 01:12:30.350
Hello?

01:13:09.139 --> 01:13:11.850
David? David?

01:13:11.892 --> 01:13:13.560
Da--

01:13:15.354 --> 01:13:17.105
David?

01:13:17.147 --> 01:13:19.107
David?

01:13:22.653 --> 01:13:24.446
David?

01:13:24.488 --> 01:13:26.865
Hello?

01:13:26.907 --> 01:13:30.285
David, are you all right?
Hey, I'll try to get you out.

01:13:32.120 --> 01:13:34.498
Here, listen, I'm gonna--

01:13:34.540 --> 01:13:37.167
shit.

01:13:37.209 --> 01:13:40.587
You hiding there, huh?
Are you all right?

01:13:41.839 --> 01:13:45.133
Hi. Everything's going to be okay.

01:13:45.175 --> 01:13:47.261
Stop it, stop--

01:13:47.302 --> 01:13:49.471
What are you doing?

01:13:51.557 --> 01:13:53.350
What are you doing?!

01:13:53.392 --> 01:13:55.602
- Ah, no!
- No, Lenny!

01:13:55.644 --> 01:13:57.855
No! Stop!

01:13:57.896 --> 01:14:00.607
No no!

01:14:16.373 --> 01:14:19.793
Ooh, what happened?

01:14:22.337 --> 01:14:24.965
- He's still alive. We can drain him.
- Not him.

01:14:27.050 --> 01:14:29.344
Aren't you the one who said
they're just cattle to us

01:14:29.386 --> 01:14:31.346
and nothing else?

01:14:34.600 --> 01:14:37.978
- Just do what you want.
- Look at this.

01:14:43.650 --> 01:14:46.486
So, I guess he took her
with him?

01:14:46.528 --> 01:14:48.405
Fuck!

01:14:48.447 --> 01:14:50.365
I didn't know the little fucker
had it in him.

01:14:53.911 --> 01:14:56.371
I'm actually
kind of proud of the kid.

01:14:56.413 --> 01:14:58.415
Yeah, well, he's gonna
get himself in trouble.

01:14:58.457 --> 01:15:00.959
He's right on the verge.

01:15:01.001 --> 01:15:03.212
We've gotta find him.

01:15:03.253 --> 01:15:05.923
Maybe you should
go get him.

01:15:07.174 --> 01:15:09.051
He looks up to you.

01:15:25.609 --> 01:15:28.153
Will you still help me
out there?

01:15:34.368 --> 01:15:36.620
Francis,

01:15:36.662 --> 01:15:38.664
where are we?

01:15:43.043 --> 01:15:45.045
We're hiding.

01:15:47.089 --> 01:15:49.633
Are you okay?

01:15:52.302 --> 01:15:54.847
We should get some help.

01:15:56.014 --> 01:15:59.560
Francis,
I need your help.

01:15:59.601 --> 01:16:02.563
I can't come near you.

01:16:04.982 --> 01:16:08.235
Francis, I can't hear you.
What?

01:16:08.277 --> 01:16:11.154
What did you say,
Francis?

01:16:11.196 --> 01:16:13.949
You're bleeding.

01:16:13.991 --> 01:16:17.911
Francis, you're scaring me.

01:16:19.496 --> 01:16:22.124
There's something
I need to tell you.

01:16:22.165 --> 01:16:24.418
Please-- please,

01:16:24.459 --> 01:16:27.129
just help me get up.

01:16:27.171 --> 01:16:29.798
We need to get help.

01:16:34.678 --> 01:16:37.139
We're born, not made.

01:16:40.267 --> 01:16:43.437
- Not like everybody thinks.
- I don't understand.

01:16:43.478 --> 01:16:46.356
Oh Christ,
let me go.

01:16:46.398 --> 01:16:48.150
Please, please--

01:16:49.526 --> 01:16:51.528
Not like the fucking movies.

01:16:51.570 --> 01:16:53.947
Francis, please stop.

01:16:53.989 --> 01:16:55.657
You have to go.

01:16:55.699 --> 01:16:58.702
Francis, please
don't do this.

01:17:27.231 --> 01:17:29.191
Franny.

01:17:29.233 --> 01:17:31.860
Franny.

01:17:37.074 --> 01:17:39.201
I know.

01:17:39.243 --> 01:17:41.495
We all gotta go
through it our first time.

01:17:44.373 --> 01:17:46.542
It's just the way
it is, okay?

01:17:51.964 --> 01:17:55.717
- I wish Mom and Dad were here.
- It just hurts so bad, David.

01:17:55.759 --> 01:17:58.720
I know, I know.

01:17:58.762 --> 01:18:01.265
It's just part
of growing up, okay?

01:18:03.267 --> 01:18:05.269
It's what we are.

01:18:52.900 --> 01:18:55.611
What does it mean
to be happy?

01:19:00.240 --> 01:19:02.951
To be content
in the world around you?

01:19:17.591 --> 01:19:20.219
Is family the heart
of everything--

01:19:24.181 --> 01:19:26.683
even existence?

01:19:50.290 --> 01:19:52.584
So what do we do now?

01:19:54.378 --> 01:19:56.380
We have to move again.

01:19:59.091 --> 01:20:01.093
The twins are packing up
the house.

01:20:01.134 --> 01:20:03.178
We're gonna leave
in a few hours.

01:20:12.521 --> 01:20:14.606
What about Lenny?

01:20:16.316 --> 01:20:18.610
We're gonna have to bring him
out of the box early.

01:20:21.738 --> 01:20:23.740
Will he be okay?

01:20:24.867 --> 01:20:27.077
You were brought
out of the box early.

01:20:29.580 --> 01:20:31.874
I was?

01:20:31.915 --> 01:20:34.001
Yeah. See how
you turned out?

01:20:37.254 --> 01:20:40.174
- Dave?
- Yeah?

01:20:42.593 --> 01:20:44.595
I'm sorry.

01:20:47.055 --> 01:20:49.016
So am I, Francis.

01:20:55.731 --> 01:20:58.567
- Are you ready?
- Okay.

01:21:01.028 --> 01:21:03.655
You guys, I really
hate keeping him like this.

01:21:03.697 --> 01:21:05.032
You know it's the way
it's always been.

01:21:05.073 --> 01:21:06.533
He would've
killed everything in sight.

01:21:06.617 --> 01:21:08.368
- Kind of like us. You ready, David?
- Let me do this.

01:21:08.410 --> 01:21:10.329
We're gonna open the door.
We don't have time for this.

01:21:10.370 --> 01:21:11.705
- This is Lenny!
- Darlene, come on.

01:21:11.747 --> 01:21:15.125
- David, let's go!
- He is-- he is our family!

01:21:15.167 --> 01:21:17.211
I can do this.

01:21:19.922 --> 01:21:22.216
Okay.

01:21:23.717 --> 01:21:25.719
Are you sure?

01:21:27.721 --> 01:21:29.723
Fine.

01:21:34.603 --> 01:21:36.563
Lenny?

01:21:39.733 --> 01:21:41.735
Lenny?

01:21:43.862 --> 01:21:45.614
Lenny?

01:21:46.657 --> 01:21:49.243
Hey, baby.

01:21:54.665 --> 01:21:56.959
Excited?

01:21:57.000 --> 01:21:59.211
Hey, baby.

01:22:01.713 --> 01:22:04.007
You see?

01:23:09.114 --> 01:23:11.742
We live with a disease.

01:23:13.660 --> 01:23:17.164
Mom used to say it was
the one thing that kept us close.

01:23:18.373 --> 01:23:21.460
I always thought that it was the one
thing that would keep us apart.

01:23:22.836 --> 01:23:25.047
But I was wrong,

01:23:25.088 --> 01:23:28.967
and everything you thought
you knew about us is wrong.

01:23:30.427 --> 01:23:33.055
We live in the houses
next to you,

01:23:33.096 --> 01:23:36.183
we work in the stores
you shop at.

01:23:36.225 --> 01:23:39.061
Our kids play with your kids.

01:23:41.230 --> 01:23:44.107
We're just trying to be
an ordinary family,

01:23:44.149 --> 01:23:47.945
trying to figure out
where we fit in in the world.

01:23:59.331 --> 01:24:03.335
But we do need blood,
and we need a lot of it...

01:24:08.966 --> 01:24:11.927
...preferably fresh
and not frozen.

01:24:11.969 --> 01:24:14.346
Howdy.

01:24:14.388 --> 01:24:16.640
We're the Thompsons.

